22/08/2003
BEIJING, China -- Romanian President Ion Iliescu's ongoing visit to China suggests better bilateral economic relations, according to reports in both the Romanian and Chinese press. During their meeting in Beijing, Iliescu and his Chinese counterpart, Hu Jintao, signed a joint declaration to enhance bilateral co-operation. It was also reported that Romania and China plan to establish a joint venture for fixed-line telephony services. Romania's Postelecom and China's ZTE Corporation sealed an 89m euro agreement Thursday (21 August) on supplying equipment to Romania. ZTE will also buy 29 per cent of Romanian Post's stake in Postelecom. The two sides also agreed to improve bilateral co-operation in the IT industry. (Rompres, Xinhua Econ Info - 22/08/03)
